1
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:10,353
Jo, are you ready?

2
00:01:10,354 --> 00:01:13,322
Hey, baby. No, no - um...
Yes, I'm all set.

3
00:01:13,615 --> 00:01:15,115
Why don't you get something to eat?

4
00:01:16,868 --> 00:01:18,368
Jo, we're already late.

5
00:01:38,973 --> 00:01:40,516
Did you grab a bottle of wine?

6
00:02:01,037 --> 00:02:04,206
If we get hitten, you could lose an eye.

7
00:02:08,169 --> 00:02:09,920
Not todayÃ‰

8
00:02:11,923 --> 00:02:13,674
How was your day?

9
00:02:14,692 --> 00:02:16,075
My day was fine.

10
00:02:27,772 --> 00:02:29,139
Thank you.

11
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:36,822
Michael where's the wine?
What?

12
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:40,117
Wine.
Shit!

13
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:46,819
Wait, wait, wait...

14
00:02:47,320 --> 00:02:48,625
Hello!

15
00:02:51,838 --> 00:02:53,922
You look nice baby.
Thanks.

16
00:02:58,178 --> 00:02:59,519
Come.

17
00:03:11,649 --> 00:03:13,000
I love you.

18
00:03:14,527 --> 00:03:17,196
Oh, you didn't bring Sarah?
You didn't tell her?

19
00:03:17,322 --> 00:03:19,719
See you in hour.
You should be finished by then.

20
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,116
Oh well, thank you for that!

21
00:03:21,743 --> 00:03:24,036
Barbara! Hello!
Thanks for having us.

22
00:03:24,162 --> 00:03:25,829
Come see me upstairs.
I will.

23
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:29,416
How long were you two together?
Three months.

24
00:03:29,542 --> 00:03:32,252
Three months?
Three months already?

25
00:03:33,088 --> 00:03:36,715
Talking to Monroe, I think we should schedule
another meeting for Monday.

26
00:03:37,759 --> 00:03:39,301
Okay, let's just see how tomorrow goes.

27
00:03:39,327 --> 00:03:42,779
I bet you didn't like Sarah either, did you?
I did! I said I did!

28
00:03:42,805 --> 00:03:44,473
Yeah, but I don't think that you meant it.

29
00:03:46,551 --> 00:03:47,951
Thanks.
Welcome.

30
00:03:47,977 --> 00:03:49,394
Why's it so hard for me, Jo?

31
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:52,856
It isn't. I mean it can't be.
You haven't gone to the hard bit yet.

32
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:54,441
What it gets harder than this?
- Joanna?

33
00:03:54,567 --> 00:03:57,027
Hello!
Hi, so good to see you.

34
00:03:57,153 --> 00:03:58,904
Thank you for having us.

35
00:03:59,030 --> 00:04:00,447
Andy...
Stuart...

36
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:05,119
Michael says you're working on a new book.

37
00:04:05,219 --> 00:04:06,664
Michael always says that.

38
00:04:09,165 --> 00:04:10,540
He's probably right.

39
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:13,585
I just don't know it?

40
00:04:15,797 --> 00:04:17,969
Well, I got to go and talk to somebody.

41
00:04:17,970 --> 00:04:19,341
Eat, I'll be here.

42
00:04:19,351 --> 00:04:21,143
He hates me.
He's gonna fire me. I know.

43
00:04:21,169 --> 00:04:23,220
You say that every week.
Yeah well, it's true.

44
00:04:23,221 --> 00:04:24,972
But it hasn't been in the last two years.

45
00:04:24,973 --> 00:04:26,842
Well maybe he's just waiting for the right time.

46
00:04:26,843 --> 00:04:29,434
Hey do you want me to walk Lucy,
while you guys are away?

47
00:04:29,460 --> 00:04:30,978
Yeah, that'd be great.

48
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,397
Where is Michael anyway?

49
00:04:34,806 --> 00:04:36,116
Here he is.

50
00:04:37,204 --> 00:04:38,517
Here he is, let's go!

51
00:04:39,570 --> 00:04:42,489
Joanna?
Um yes no I'm going to go to the ladies.

52
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:45,409
I'll catch you up.
Okay.

53
00:05:14,314 --> 00:05:17,065
I'm starving.

54
00:05:19,735 --> 00:05:22,779
Hey, where have you guys been?
I got totally ambushed by Stuart.

55
00:05:22,780 --> 00:05:24,400
The guy's hasn't talked to me in two weeks -

56
00:05:24,407 --> 00:05:26,616
- and sees me with your wife,
and just lit up.

57
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:33,232
Laura, this is my Joanna.
Hello! Nice to meet you.

58
00:05:33,233 --> 00:05:35,992
Joanna, this is Laura. She's our new designer,
who has worked for us.

59
00:05:36,418 --> 00:05:38,170
Nice to finally meet you.

60
00:05:38,596 --> 00:05:41,089
So Michael tells me you're a writer.
Yes, I am.

61
00:05:41,215 --> 00:05:44,426
I've been meaning to order your book.
That's nice.

62
00:05:44,552 --> 00:05:48,096
Oh! Look, look! Oh my god!
Neal he's trying with Cynthia again.

63
00:05:48,097 --> 00:05:50,599
She's not going to go for it.
I know. It just won't work.

64
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:52,091
Why not?
He's a good looking guy.

65
00:05:52,693 --> 00:05:54,728
Why did you turn him down?

66
00:05:54,754 --> 00:05:56,079
Speak of the devil...

67
00:05:56,105 --> 00:05:58,198
Hey, Neal!
Had any luck with Cynthia?

68
00:05:58,199 --> 00:05:59,999
Hi Joanna!
Hello.

69
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,600
Had any luck?
What?

70
00:06:02,570 --> 00:06:04,780
You didn't really go to
"The Yogo" with her, did you?

71
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,825
She told you that?
She told me about that!

72
00:06:07,851 --> 00:06:11,411
Still with Cynthia huh?
What? You're getting jealous?

73
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:15,332
So what's Laura's story ?

74
00:06:15,458 --> 00:06:18,585
Stuart recruited her.
She seems to be good.

75
00:06:19,939 --> 00:06:23,024
She's working the Monroe project with us.

76
00:06:25,525 --> 00:06:27,110
Of course she is...

77
00:06:31,794 --> 00:06:33,719
Try to get me some wine?

78
00:06:49,117 --> 00:06:50,909
That's not funny.

79
00:06:59,124 --> 00:07:01,803
There you go.
Hi. Would you like a drink?

80
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:04,231
Yeah, white wine please.
Sure.

81
00:07:05,758 --> 00:07:07,134
Thanks.

82
00:07:10,054 --> 00:07:12,451
Is she going to Philadelphia with you guys tomorrow?

83
00:07:12,852 --> 00:07:14,249
Yeah.

84
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:17,978
And she was in LA with
Michael last month?

85
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:28,822
Taxi!

86
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:34,077
Have you been smoking?

87
00:07:35,746 --> 00:07:38,457
You really going to attempt to give me
a grief about that?

88
00:07:40,585 --> 00:07:42,035
What's wrong?

89
00:07:42,837 --> 00:07:44,187
Nothing.

90
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:49,885
Have I done something wrong?

91
00:08:55,139 --> 00:08:57,186
She is pretty.
Who?

92
00:08:58,996 --> 00:09:00,651
You never mentioned that.

93
00:09:00,652 --> 00:09:02,707
Laura?
Yeah, Laura.

94
00:09:03,668 --> 00:09:05,877
I think you described her as "whatever".

95
00:09:06,462 --> 00:09:08,922
I don't remember.
I bet.

96
00:09:14,804 --> 00:09:17,055
You didn't tell me that she was in LA with you.

97
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:19,599
She's wasn't in LA with me.
We were just there at the same time.

98
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:21,268
Michael, face me!

99
00:09:22,353 --> 00:09:25,897
You didn't tell me anything about her, before tonight,
but then I think you know that.

100
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:27,691
What's that supposed to mean?

101
00:09:29,151 --> 00:09:31,570
What did you think could happen tonight?

102
00:09:32,029 --> 00:09:34,948
And seriously, did you think I just wouldn't notice?

103
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:37,617
Why would I think anything would make you notice her?

104
00:09:37,827 --> 00:09:39,619
You're a terrible liar!

105
00:09:39,790 --> 00:09:41,371
Might be because
I don't l lie.

106
00:09:41,497 --> 00:09:43,707
She likes you,
and you like her.

107
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:46,208
Of course you don't want to talk to me
about it.

108
00:09:46,610 --> 00:09:48,927
Where is this come from?
My eyes, Michael!

109
00:09:49,128 --> 00:09:51,628
She's she the only one you talked to,
all night.

110
00:09:51,908 --> 00:09:53,967
How many glasses of wine did you have
tonight, Jo?

111
00:09:53,993 --> 00:09:56,795
Two and two sips.
Is that really your response?

112
00:09:56,821 --> 00:09:58,330
You had more than that.

113
00:09:58,356 --> 00:10:00,765
What are you?
The drink patrol?

114
00:10:00,891 --> 00:10:03,977
Well remind me when we go out,
and I ask you not to have another.

115
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:06,521
You ask me why.
This is why.

116
00:10:06,647 --> 00:10:10,066
You're kidding me, right?
Because it makes you like this, baby.

117
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:15,071
Michael without wine we would be in a
much shittier place.

118
00:10:15,681 --> 00:10:18,867
Eleven hours a day.
Five, sometimes six days a week.

119
00:10:18,993 --> 00:10:23,496
That's sixty hours a week with her,
three months now.

120
00:10:23,956 --> 00:10:28,501
What is it you think I have done?
Check my phone, Jo.

121
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:30,996
And check my e-mails, check receipts, go on.

122
00:10:31,122 --> 00:10:33,673
Not everyone gets caught, Michael.

123
00:10:35,926 --> 00:10:37,886
Has she told you she's attracted to you?

124
00:10:38,220 --> 00:10:39,971
Maybe, Joanna.

125
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:42,932
I don't let the conversation go there.

126
00:10:43,059 --> 00:10:44,851
But she tried to, hasn't she?

127
00:10:44,977 --> 00:10:47,604
But she tried to when you were
in LA together?

128
00:10:47,730 --> 00:10:50,774
You do hours I do not know about,
with the people that you work with.

129
00:10:51,525 --> 00:10:53,485
You go away -

130
00:10:53,736 --> 00:10:57,072
- doing articles, all the time!

131
00:10:59,325 --> 00:11:03,703
Have I ever given you a reason to stand here
feeling the way that I am right now?

132
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:08,650
I looked through a window tonight and I
saw something that I didn't need to see.

133
00:11:08,676 --> 00:11:10,639
Couldn't you just have watched yourself
and spared me?

134
00:11:10,640 --> 00:11:12,003
What the fuck are you doing!?

135
00:11:12,004 --> 00:11:14,939
I want to charge the phone.
Why do you always have to use this one?

136
00:11:14,965 --> 00:11:17,509
Why did you build a Berlin wall of freakin' magazines!?

137
00:11:20,304 --> 00:11:24,724
I haven't done anything wrong,
and you try to pick a fight.

138
00:11:26,435 --> 00:11:27,977
I spare you.

139
00:11:33,734 --> 00:11:35,126
I would.

140
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,471
What's that supposed to mean?

141
00:11:43,472 --> 00:11:45,161
What's that supposed to mean?

142
00:11:47,873 --> 00:11:51,009
Is she going to Philadelphia with you and Andy tomorrow?

143
00:11:51,269 --> 00:11:53,461
Uh-huh, cause she's been working on
the Monroe properly with us.

144
00:11:55,131 --> 00:11:57,006
Why? What does that look?

145
00:11:58,486 --> 00:12:00,007
That looks sad, Michael.

146
00:12:00,594 --> 00:12:03,888
There's nothing going on,  Jo.
Laura is just someone I work with.

147
00:12:06,183 --> 00:12:10,152
It's not that I'm blaming you for being
attracted to her. She's... -

148
00:12:10,153 --> 00:12:11,521
- attractive.

149
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:16,985
And it's natural to crave newness.

150
00:12:25,161 --> 00:12:26,745
So what are you blaming me for?

151
00:12:28,122 --> 00:12:30,457
For going out of your way not to admit it.

152
00:12:33,043 --> 00:12:35,086
Thought I just did.

153
00:12:39,091 --> 00:12:41,301
Don't do that face, Jo...

154
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:49,684
You know what I meant.

155
00:12:51,937 --> 00:12:54,814
You corner me, and you order me
to admit something -

156
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:58,985
and then you're pouncing me the second I came,
and now you're going to sleep on the couch?

157
00:12:59,361 --> 00:13:00,945
Fucking fantastic!

158
00:13:03,199 --> 00:13:05,241
I did not do anything wrong, Jo.

159
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:36,105
I'm sorry.

160
00:13:38,192 --> 00:13:39,526
What for?

161
00:13:40,694 --> 00:13:44,280
I'm not sure but,
I love you.

162
00:13:45,616 --> 00:13:47,008
Come to bed.

163
00:13:48,077 --> 00:13:49,494
I don't want to.

164
00:13:53,999 --> 00:13:55,708
Come to the kitchen.

165
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,752
Food isn't going to fix this.

166
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:00,012
Soon you'll have a full stomach.
Come on.

167
00:14:02,716 --> 00:14:05,468
We got any tomatoes?
No.

168
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:28,616
How was your day?

169
00:14:28,742 --> 00:14:31,995
Oh, but...

170
00:14:33,497 --> 00:14:36,124
What?
Nothing,  I just remembered I'm mad at you.

171
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,834
I hate it when that happens.

172
00:14:40,462 --> 00:14:42,000
Danny proposed!

173
00:14:42,001 --> 00:14:43,339
Yeah!

174
00:14:43,465 --> 00:14:45,884
What Pia said?
What did you think she said? Yes!

175
00:14:45,910 --> 00:14:47,251
Was she surprised at all?

176
00:14:47,277 --> 00:14:49,762
Yes, she thought that he was going to tell her
he was moving out.

177
00:15:00,691 --> 00:15:03,985
My mum called.
Yeah, I know. I spoked to her.

178
00:15:04,737 --> 00:15:07,657
Second week of December.
I' ve already said yes.

179
00:15:09,283 --> 00:15:12,327
Can we go via London?
Yeah, sure.

180
00:15:15,372 --> 00:15:18,082
What time is your train?
At 8:00.

181
00:15:18,208 --> 00:15:20,293
You shouldn't be up this late.

182
00:15:20,419 --> 00:15:21,836
I'll sleep on the train.

183
00:15:21,837 --> 00:15:24,811
It's an hours ride.
I'll sleep in the meeting.

184
00:15:26,717 --> 00:15:28,718
What are you doing tomorrow or today?

185
00:15:29,178 --> 00:15:31,171
I got to finish up the accessories piece.

186
00:15:31,172 --> 00:15:32,864
Yeah, with pearls?

187
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:35,642
Yeah, I'll dig up another hundred words.

188
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:39,479
It's good. And then you can work on the book,
without me here to distract you.

189
00:15:45,861 --> 00:15:47,403
Joanna, I'm sorry.

190
00:15:48,030 --> 00:15:51,366
I would have said something about her,
if I thought there was something to say.

191
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:56,612
Michael, did something happen in LA?

192
00:15:56,613 --> 00:15:57,964
No.

193
00:16:00,668 --> 00:16:03,086
I swear.
No.

194
00:16:07,091 --> 00:16:08,591
Eggs are good.

195
00:16:11,011 --> 00:16:12,387
Yeah.

196
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:25,108
What about the orange juice?

197
00:16:25,409 --> 00:16:27,151
Come on.
What kind of cafe is this?

198
00:16:37,287 --> 00:16:39,580
Do you think we got married too soon?

199
00:16:43,419 --> 00:16:44,745
What?

200
00:16:45,246 --> 00:16:47,672
Why can't you make yourself consider that?

201
00:16:49,633 --> 00:16:51,342
Because I don't have to.

202
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:55,013
I don't think we got married too soon -

203
00:16:55,139 --> 00:16:57,181
- because we married after four years.

204
00:16:57,307 --> 00:16:59,726
Yeah, with a break up in the middle.

205
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:03,479
And anyway, it's not about the amount of time
but the when of time -

206
00:17:03,605 --> 00:17:06,482
- and our when included college.

207
00:17:08,044 --> 00:17:10,583
You know, that was before we were even us, you know.

208
00:17:13,407 --> 00:17:16,576
Do you think it's even the same
between us?

209
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:20,621
It got better...

210
00:17:23,540 --> 00:17:26,335
Can you hear yourself right now?

211
00:17:29,173 --> 00:17:30,506
What?

212
00:17:31,432 --> 00:17:35,970
Just because I disagree with you,
means I'm not aware of what I'm saying?

213
00:17:36,096 --> 00:17:37,930
You can't really think that.

214
00:17:38,307 --> 00:17:40,975
I do think that.
How?

215
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:44,645
Sunday night.
The last two weekends.

216
00:17:44,772 --> 00:17:47,565
Breakfast yesterday.
Dinner last night.

217
00:17:47,775 --> 00:17:49,776
There's no bullshit between us.

218
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:54,363
With the possible exception of this evening.

219
00:17:59,536 --> 00:18:02,288
Come here, Jo.
I'm cold.

220
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:12,775
Got your orange juice?
No. Thank you!

221
00:19:35,799 --> 00:19:38,968
You're gonna try to get some writing done?
"Try" is a big word.

222
00:19:39,094 --> 00:19:40,444
No, it's not.

223
00:19:44,391 --> 00:19:48,186
Alright, I got to go.
See you later.

224
00:19:48,979 --> 00:19:50,313
Bye.

225
00:20:56,588 --> 00:20:58,589
Hello.
A cup of coffee, please.

226
00:21:14,898 --> 00:21:16,248
Joanna!

227
00:21:20,862 --> 00:21:23,364
Alex! What are you doing here?

228
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:24,865
I have some work here.

229
00:21:28,159 --> 00:21:29,578
I can't believe this!

230
00:21:29,830 --> 00:21:32,540
Yeah, it's been a while.
How are you?

231
00:21:32,708 --> 00:21:37,628
I'm fine, I just can't believe you're here.
How did you know I'd be here?

232
00:21:37,754 --> 00:21:39,447
I keep tabs on you.

233
00:21:39,448 --> 00:21:41,340
I'm serious.
So am I.

234
00:21:42,718 --> 00:21:45,886
Your Christmas cards.
They gave the return address on them.

235
00:21:46,013 --> 00:21:48,806
What if I' d moved?
You haven' t.

236
00:21:50,100 --> 00:21:51,976
How long are you in New York for?

237
00:21:52,102 --> 00:21:55,479
I leave tomorrow. Actually, I'm late for a meeting.

238
00:21:57,107 --> 00:21:58,899
Do you have time for me now?

239
00:21:59,651 --> 00:22:02,862
Yeah, yeah. Sure.
Good.

240
00:22:02,988 --> 00:22:05,614
Then I call you later with the time.

241
00:22:05,741 --> 00:22:08,242
Wait, wait, do you need my number?
Has it changed?

242
00:22:09,453 --> 00:22:10,828
No...

243
00:22:11,455 --> 00:22:13,080
Then I call you later?

244
00:22:15,959 --> 00:22:17,418
Wait!

245
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:52,378
Cause I've never been able to sleep -

246
00:22:52,379 --> 00:22:55,180
- think that by the time I sleep I won't wake up
for about four years.

247
00:22:55,206 --> 00:22:57,083
Be like, ...

248
00:22:58,335 --> 00:23:00,330
I need to use the men's room.
Okay.

249
00:23:00,467 --> 00:23:02,797
Michael, we have to wait for Andy.

250
00:23:03,739 --> 00:23:07,028
It's funny, because I could actually.. I could sleep anywhere.

251
00:23:07,060 --> 00:23:09,449
Is that right?
Yes, I could probably fall sleep right here.

252
00:23:09,450 --> 00:23:10,838
Right here?

