00:42:12,613 --> 00:42:16,282
I didn't move.
I wouldn't have.

511
00:42:38,389 --> 00:42:40,014
I'm married.

512
00:42:40,140 --> 00:42:41,507
I know.

513
00:42:44,096 --> 00:42:45,631
Still it felt nice.

514
00:42:51,385 --> 00:42:55,098
That is so embarrassing!
Thank you.

515
00:42:55,456 --> 00:42:57,378
Usually she's doing it better.

516
00:42:57,379 --> 00:42:59,701
No, the point was that I love Italy.

517
00:42:59,827 --> 00:43:03,413
I love it there.
We have a place, we go there -

518
00:43:03,539 --> 00:43:06,457
- one month a year.
It's so wonderful.

519
00:43:06,458 --> 00:43:08,958
Wait! This is who you went to Italy with?
When?

520
00:43:09,512 --> 00:43:11,121
When I got to Paris early, and -

521
00:43:11,147 --> 00:43:13,840
- your little cousin was staying in the apartment,
till you got back -

522
00:43:13,966 --> 00:43:16,801
- and you were away with Patrick and his friends.

523
00:43:16,927 --> 00:43:18,386
Yeah, exactly!
This is them.

524
00:43:19,430 --> 00:43:22,890
That's really so weird!
And you seemed familiar!

525
00:43:23,392 --> 00:43:24,726
How funny.

526
00:43:29,481 --> 00:43:31,357
What if you were married?

527
00:43:33,319 --> 00:43:36,487
Hypotheticals don't do much for me, but...

528
00:43:38,490 --> 00:43:40,533
Probably nothing different.

529
00:43:45,623 --> 00:43:48,499
Are you happy?
With what?

530
00:43:50,044 --> 00:43:53,129
With your marriage.
Yeah.

531
00:43:55,257 --> 00:43:56,558
Very.

532
00:43:59,345 --> 00:44:01,846
You can be happy and still be tempted.

533
00:44:02,348 --> 00:44:03,689
I know.

534
00:44:05,434 --> 00:44:07,393
Just surprised you do.

535
00:44:11,273 --> 00:44:13,858
Have you ever been with someone else
since you've been married?

536
00:44:15,235 --> 00:44:16,611
No.

537
00:44:17,071 --> 00:44:19,739
Have you wanted to be?

538
00:44:23,116 --> 00:44:24,452
What happened?

539
00:44:26,997 --> 00:44:28,748
Think of Joanna.

540
00:44:31,627 --> 00:44:34,337
You regret not doing it?

541
00:44:37,341 --> 00:44:40,093
I'd regret more if I did.

542
00:44:52,106 --> 00:44:53,690
You ever cheated on anybody?

543
00:44:54,400 --> 00:44:56,484
Cheated?

544
00:44:56,610 --> 00:44:58,027
Have you?

545
00:44:58,904 --> 00:45:00,229
No.

546
00:45:01,782 --> 00:45:04,826
Not necessarily on principle,
I just -

547
00:45:05,119 --> 00:45:06,577
- I never wanted to.

548
00:45:11,125 --> 00:45:15,002
Alex, I know you want them.
I need one yeah.

549
00:45:17,047 --> 00:45:18,464
And I know you want one.

550
00:45:18,590 --> 00:45:21,384
No, no, no.
She wants to keep me company.

551
00:45:21,385 --> 00:45:23,953
I do. I do.
You do? I do.

552
00:45:25,305 --> 00:45:26,681
Okay.
So have a good night.

553
00:45:28,182 --> 00:45:30,186
It's a trap.
I know.

554
00:45:31,187 --> 00:45:33,116
You'll never change.

555
00:45:35,357 --> 00:45:40,027
When was the last time you saw Alex?
Two years ago.

556
00:45:40,237 --> 00:45:41,904
So you know Helen?

557
00:45:43,332 --> 00:45:44,632
Helen?

558
00:45:44,658 --> 00:45:46,784
Alex's girlfriend from Paris.

559
00:45:50,205 --> 00:45:53,708
Well, we are not very good at keeping touch with -

560
00:45:53,834 --> 00:45:58,254
- the dailies.
We talk when we talk.

561
00:45:59,207 --> 00:46:03,468
She's nice. I don't think he's going
to settle down with her anytime soon.

562
00:46:04,386 --> 00:46:07,847
But I don't know that Alex would ever settle down,
with anyone.

563
00:46:08,182 --> 00:46:10,725
He seems more whole,
on his own.

564
00:46:12,603 --> 00:46:14,353
So where is your husband?

565
00:46:14,354 --> 00:46:16,954
He's in Philidelphia on a business trip.

566
00:46:19,401 --> 00:46:20,777
What's he do?

567
00:46:20,903 --> 00:46:22,820
Commercial real estate development -

568
00:46:22,846 --> 00:46:26,491
- but, I don't think this was the question
you wanted to ask.

569
00:46:26,617 --> 00:46:30,203
No, it wasn't.
Go ahead.

570
00:46:30,329 --> 00:46:32,205
I usually tend to go too far.

571
00:46:33,415 --> 00:46:35,124
Okay, warning heard.

572
00:46:35,250 --> 00:46:37,168
Does your husband know Alex?

573
00:46:40,839 --> 00:46:42,256
No.

574
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:45,009
Does he know of him?
No.

575
00:46:45,761 --> 00:46:49,430
Have I gone too far?
Yeah, maybe, but it's fun!

576
00:46:50,933 --> 00:46:52,934
Why haven't you told him?

577
00:46:55,395 --> 00:46:59,982
I think when you know something like that,
you can't unlearn it.

578
00:47:00,984 --> 00:47:03,277
So there is a something like that.

579
00:47:05,614 --> 00:47:07,782
Are you faithful?
Yes.

580
00:47:10,285 --> 00:47:12,578
Will he forgive you,
if you were not?

581
00:47:13,413 --> 00:47:15,456
He's always said
that he wouldn't.

582
00:47:16,458 --> 00:47:18,292
Does that stop you?

583
00:47:20,045 --> 00:47:22,255
Yeah, probably.

584
00:47:22,881 --> 00:47:25,925
How long were you with Alex together?

585
00:47:26,051 --> 00:47:27,927
We were never really together.

586
00:47:28,053 --> 00:47:31,180
We were more kind of on and off.

587
00:47:33,058 --> 00:47:35,601
You think you'll tell your husband
about tonight?

588
00:47:37,020 --> 00:47:39,814
I don't know.
Tonight is not finished yet.

589
00:47:59,443 --> 00:48:02,254
Remember the last time we were here,
and we got in the wrong car?

590
00:48:02,280 --> 00:48:04,247
When was that?
Remember how far we went before you remembered?

591
00:48:04,248 --> 00:48:06,215
Ten blocks. Hey guys, come on.

592
00:48:06,341 --> 00:48:07,734
Why don't you just drive with us?

593
00:48:07,785 --> 00:48:10,261
Oh shit, Lucy!
Who?

594
00:48:10,387 --> 00:48:13,431
A friend's dog.
I said I'd walk her.

595
00:48:13,557 --> 00:48:14,974
Where is she?

596
00:48:15,350 --> 00:48:16,684
She's on our friend's apartment.

597
00:48:17,561 --> 00:48:19,437
Are you just saying that to get out of
going to the party?

598
00:48:19,563 --> 00:48:21,772
No, No! I know! I swear!

599
00:48:24,109 --> 00:48:26,277
When were you last in New York?

600
00:48:27,571 --> 00:48:30,072
Nine months ago.

601
00:48:30,365 --> 00:48:32,700
Why didn't you get in touch?

602
00:48:34,703 --> 00:48:38,706
I wasn't alone...

603
00:49:19,373 --> 00:49:21,415
Can't get the key out!

604
00:49:56,785 --> 00:49:58,160
Andy cooks?

605
00:49:58,286 --> 00:50:02,373
No, I bought that for him last year
I doubt he's ever used it.

606
00:50:03,250 --> 00:50:05,001
I do that when we're over.

607
00:50:05,127 --> 00:50:07,169
So why aren't you writing?

608
00:50:07,921 --> 00:50:09,463
I am writing!

609
00:50:09,589 --> 00:50:10,903
No, why aren't you writing?

610
00:50:10,904 --> 00:50:13,217
You mean...
Your book, Joanna.

611
00:50:16,054 --> 00:50:20,349
My editor says that I just need to get over
my doubt.

612
00:50:21,601 --> 00:50:25,062
What do you doubt?
Everything, Alex.

613
00:50:26,273 --> 00:50:29,066
I go to write -

614
00:50:29,192 --> 00:50:33,362
- and every word, every thought, every choice
that I make leads to another and -

615
00:50:33,488 --> 00:50:35,614
- I doubt every single one I make.

616
00:50:35,866 --> 00:50:37,658
It wasn't like this last time.

617
00:50:38,360 --> 00:50:41,078
You live with your first book
all your life -

618
00:50:41,704 --> 00:50:43,380
- it comes out on its own.

619
00:50:44,624 --> 00:50:48,002
After that though, it's just different.
You can suddenly write -

620
00:50:48,128 --> 00:50:51,714
- anything and you second-guess everything.

621
00:50:53,175 --> 00:50:57,762
Doubts will kill your work.
Who me? I don't know.

622
00:50:58,680 --> 00:51:00,598
What's the matter with doubt?

623
00:51:01,141 --> 00:51:03,568
I think the world could use
a little more doubt.

624
00:51:03,594 --> 00:51:04,977
So I doubt...

625
00:51:05,003 --> 00:51:06,771
For the good of the world?

626
00:51:06,980 --> 00:51:08,439
Exactly.

627
00:51:08,690 --> 00:51:10,024
No, thank you.

628
00:51:11,985 --> 00:51:13,861
Your first book was good, Joanna.

629
00:51:19,367 --> 00:51:21,744
You know I think you might just have ruined
this kitchen for me.

630
00:51:23,080 --> 00:51:24,468
How?

631
00:51:24,869 --> 00:51:26,457
By being in it.

632
00:51:29,044 --> 00:51:31,587
I come here all the time,
and now you've been here.

633
00:51:44,409 --> 00:51:46,602
Remind me why it didn't work?

634
00:51:47,479 --> 00:51:48,821
Geography.

635
00:51:48,822 --> 00:51:50,564
People live between two cities.

636
00:51:50,774 --> 00:51:52,691
I don't, and neither do you.

637
00:51:53,902 --> 00:51:55,277
And timing.

638
00:51:55,403 --> 00:51:56,946
You were broken up!

639
00:51:57,364 --> 00:52:01,325
Temporarily. Technically, whateverly...

640
00:52:01,451 --> 00:52:02,785
We got back together -

641
00:52:02,911 --> 00:52:05,913
- after we'd already been together
for a really long time.

642
00:52:06,414 --> 00:52:07,998
You came after.

643
00:52:08,125 --> 00:52:12,128
So you're with him, 
because he came first?

644
00:52:12,420 --> 00:52:15,089
He did, and I love him -

645
00:52:15,924 --> 00:52:19,426
- and I love you too, and I love
being able to tell you the truth.

646
00:52:19,719 --> 00:52:21,667
And I love...

647
00:52:21,668 --> 00:52:26,016
Faith, loyalty and all that shit, even now.

648
00:52:27,018 --> 00:52:28,352
And this?

649
00:52:30,021 --> 00:52:31,413
This?

650
00:52:33,567 --> 00:52:36,819
I don't know that this would be 
what it is on its own.

651
00:52:37,863 --> 00:52:41,999
This is only what it is, because it's something that's between -

652
00:52:42,325 --> 00:52:47,079
- me, my marriage to Michael,
you and your set of things.

653
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,834
Does Andy have anything to drink?

654
00:52:59,259 --> 00:53:02,052
What are my things?
Nothing, I'm criticizing.

655
00:53:02,304 --> 00:53:03,643
I'm just...

656
00:53:04,144 --> 00:53:07,183
I know that if we went for it,
we'd lose it.

657
00:53:07,601 --> 00:53:10,853
That's hard to lose,
because we never wear out.

658
00:53:10,979 --> 00:53:14,190
We were just getting to know,
that we weren't right for each other.

659
00:53:14,316 --> 00:53:15,709
You didn't want to!

660
00:53:15,710 --> 00:53:17,902
No.
No?

661
00:53:18,445 --> 00:53:20,779
I came to Paris for two months!

662
00:53:21,072 --> 00:53:22,381
You do hold that against me.

663
00:53:22,407 --> 00:53:26,535
I don't hold anything against you!
I was finishing a book.

664
00:53:27,245 --> 00:53:28,592
I was too tired to figure out -

665
00:53:28,593 --> 00:53:30,497
- what you being there even meant.

666
00:53:30,624 --> 00:53:34,376
It should have meant that you wanted
to spend some time with me.

667
00:53:35,295 --> 00:53:38,964
It doesn't matter.
No, it matter to me.

668
00:53:39,633 --> 00:53:41,926
Because I'm the one who has to see you here.

669
00:53:42,177 --> 00:53:44,261
I'm the one who has to look around Andy's

670
00:53:44,387 --> 00:53:46,722
- to see these pictures of you in this life.

671
00:53:48,350 --> 00:53:49,742
What?

672
00:53:50,143 --> 00:53:52,853
I was what you needed to be sure of Michael?

673
00:53:54,064 --> 00:53:57,733
No. No.
It doesn't work like that.

674
00:54:02,697 --> 00:54:04,365
I think...

675
00:54:05,951 --> 00:54:09,954
Maybe I've wanted this to change.

676
00:54:10,622 --> 00:54:12,122
Everything...

677
00:54:12,832 --> 00:54:17,461
Everything changes, but this,
this still hasn't.

678
00:54:18,630 --> 00:54:21,590
Not for me.
That's a lesson.

679
00:54:23,343 --> 00:54:26,512
I saw you this morning...

680
00:54:30,475 --> 00:54:34,561
And... in the middle of most nights, when I can't sleep -

681
00:54:35,855 --> 00:54:37,731
- I still replay you.

682
00:55:04,926 --> 00:55:06,719
I'm going to take her out for a walk.

683
00:55:57,812 --> 00:55:59,355
Keys, Alex!

684
00:56:00,398 --> 00:56:03,317
I thought you took them with you.
No.

685
00:56:04,069 --> 00:56:05,569
Oh merde!

686
00:56:05,862 --> 00:56:07,446
Did you leave them upstairs?

687
00:56:07,572 --> 00:56:10,157
Yeah, can we call someone?

688
00:56:11,783 --> 00:56:13,952
We can call Caroline, but...

689
00:56:21,451 --> 00:56:22,836
Shit!

690
00:57:24,899 --> 00:57:28,902
Give me that, I'll give it back to you tomorrow.
Let's go.

691
00:58:01,019 --> 00:58:03,645
You weren't lying about the dog!
No!

692
00:58:05,106 --> 00:58:06,823
Come with me.
Let us find Fred.

693
00:58:06,824 --> 00:58:08,141
Okay.

694
00:58:12,234 --> 00:58:15,861
Her husband's best friend's dog.

695
00:58:22,957 --> 00:58:26,585
She's the one Chris told me about?
I don't know.

696
00:58:26,711 --> 00:58:30,964
At Phillips wedding, after you just broken off
with Lauren.

697
00:58:31,925 --> 00:58:35,135
I asked him, what the hell was
wrong with you.

698
00:58:37,514 --> 00:58:39,056
I liked Lauren.

699
00:58:39,766 --> 00:58:42,768
But I like this one much more.

700
00:58:44,589 --> 00:58:47,670
She's smart.
Yeah.

701
00:58:47,705 --> 00:58:49,399
She's funny.
Yeah.

702
00:58:49,400 --> 00:58:51,900
She's gorgeous!
I know.

703
00:58:53,451 --> 00:58:54,801
And she's honest.

704
00:58:55,740 --> 00:58:59,076
Well I mean, besides the fact she's out with you,
and her husband is out of town.

705
00:59:00,328 --> 00:59:01,870
But she's married.

706
00:59:03,164 --> 00:59:07,167
I know.
No, you don't. No, you've never been married.

707
00:59:07,377 --> 00:59:09,349
I mean fuck the vows.

708
00:59:09,350 --> 00:59:11,922
 It's the years you can't undo.

709
00:59:12,423 --> 00:59:16,635
You will never be able to take her away
the years with her husband.

710
00:59:16,803 --> 00:59:21,557
And the moment you try, this,
this will be gone.

711
00:59:22,849 --> 00:59:26,103
Trust me.
That would be a shame.

712
00:59:29,482 --> 00:59:33,402
I bet you've had less than a hundred days
together, am I right?

713
00:59:36,134 --> 00:59:37,503
It's the best.

714
00:59:40,243 --> 00:59:44,329
Be smart.
Keep it as it is.

715
01:00:38,009 --> 01:00:39,314
I'm in!

716
01:00:40,215 --> 01:00:41,519
Your turn.

717
01:00:48,144 --> 01:00:49,536
Here.

718
01:00:52,523 --> 01:00:54,191
Oh, come on.

719
01:00:54,442 --> 01:00:56,985
I'm not going to be the only one in here,
in my underwear.

720
01:01:56,254 --> 01:01:58,004
You're uncomfortable.

721
01:01:58,631 --> 01:02:00,507
I am uncomfortable.

722
01:02:02,844 --> 01:02:04,678
You don't hold back much, do you?

723
01:02:04,804 --> 01:02:08,390
We're here in our underwear. I think
it's a late for that, no?

724
01:03:09,577 --> 01:03:11,745
Do you remember that first night?

725
01:03:12,538 --> 01:03:14,080
Do you ever think about it?

726
01:03:14,916 --> 01:03:16,224
Of course I do.

727
01:03:18,836 --> 01:03:22,130
I did not want to go home,
and you put me in a taxi.

728
01:03:23,683 --> 01:03:25,066
And do you remember that night -

729
01:03:25,092 --> 01:03:27,861
- when we met the photographer you were interviewing?

730
01:03:27,887 --> 01:03:30,013
And he was drunk!
He was drunk.

731
01:03:31,974 --> 01:03:34,726
And you danced on that top of yours with no back.

732
01:03:37,814 --> 01:03:39,272
Come.

733
01:04:43,880 --> 01:04:45,297
Let's go.

734
01:05:43,105 --> 01:05:46,107
So, have you ever been cheated on?

735
01:05:48,653 --> 01:05:50,003
No.

736
01:05:54,492 --> 01:05:56,076
Well, I have.

737
01:05:59,747 --> 01:06:02,332
The worst part with her I found out.

738
01:06:05,544 --> 01:06:08,380
We shared a photo account -

739
01:06:08,506 --> 01:06:11,466
- and I went on the website to order
some pictures -

740
01:06:11,801 --> 01:06:15,303
- and I saw the album she decided to
share with him.

741
01:06:16,180 --> 01:06:19,641
I think they were together for the weekend,
or something.

742
01:06:20,135 --> 01:06:23,520
I could have done without the visuals.

743
01:06:23,980 --> 01:06:28,191
There was this one, they were laughing so much...

744
01:06:31,320 --> 01:06:32,779
What happened?

745
01:06:32,905 --> 01:06:37,325
We fucked like animals for about a month.

746
01:06:38,535 --> 01:06:40,584
I was angry...

747
01:06:41,085 --> 01:06:44,833
Maybe because I thought I had to be.

748
01:06:45,960 --> 01:06:47,877
Or maybe because I was sad.

749
01:06:48,754 --> 01:06:52,841
But he still wanted to be with me,
I still wanted to be with him.

750
01:06:53,217 --> 01:06:54,567
So what happened?

751
01:06:55,720 --> 01:06:57,429
We stayed together -

752
01:06:59,617 --> 01:07:01,825
- had the best year of our relationship.

753
01:07:04,270 --> 01:07:05,662
And then?

754
01:07:09,984 --> 01:07:11,334
He died.

755
01:07:13,404 --> 01:07:14,771
I'm sorry.

756
01:07:34,008 --> 01:07:37,510
Do you want anything to drink?
No, I'm fine.

757
01:07:59,742 --> 01:08:01,951
Do you think you still would have been with him?

758
01:08:05,456 --> 01:08:09,167
Yeah, definitely.

759
01:08:12,171 --> 01:08:16,132
And I think I'd still be here, attracted to you.

760
01:08:46,080 --> 01:08:48,248
You'd never guess what I was upset about
this morning.

761
01:08:49,291 --> 01:08:52,460
Michael had a work think last night
that we went to -

762
01:08:53,337 --> 01:08:56,881
- and I was accusing him of being
attracted to this woman he's working with.

763
01:08:57,675 --> 01:08:59,843
Was he?
I think so.

764
01:09:01,554 --> 01:09:03,513
You think there's something going on?

765
01:09:03,806 --> 01:09:05,332
It could be.

766
01:09:06,133 --> 01:09:08,059
I think he'd want that to be.

767
01:09:10,361 --> 01:09:12,560
He's in Philadelphia with her right now.

768
01:09:13,315 --> 01:09:14,858
Are you worried?

769
01:09:16,527 --> 01:09:18,386
I think I make too big a deal out of it.

770
01:09:18,387 --> 01:09:19,745
Why?

771
01:09:21,323 --> 01:09:23,783
It's 2:00 in the morning and
I'm here with you.

772
01:09:28,330 --> 01:09:32,011
So when you think you could get up and have
absolutely no idea what a day will go?

773
01:09:32,459 --> 01:09:33,877
Eighty...

774
01:09:34,295 --> 01:09:38,047
Ninery, a thousand years back
without incident -

775
01:09:38,174 --> 01:09:39,799
- and then all of a sudden...

776
01:09:40,342 --> 01:09:42,677
Hello!
Hello!

777
01:09:44,930 --> 01:09:47,432
What if I hadn't come up for coffee
this morning?

778
01:09:48,475 --> 01:09:50,351
I would have called.

779
01:09:51,020 --> 01:09:53,146
If my number changed?

780
01:09:54,690 --> 01:09:56,649
I would have come upstairs.

781
01:09:57,651 --> 01:09:59,235
What about Michael?

782
01:10:08,245 --> 01:10:10,496
Why did you stop e-mailing me?

783
01:10:16,378 --> 01:10:18,338
Because it wasn't enough...

784
01:10:22,676 --> 01:10:26,429
Do you know how often I have to make a choice,
not to write.

785
01:10:27,139 --> 01:10:29,349
"Hello, Alex. How are you?".

786
01:10:29,350 --> 01:10:31,559
"Where are you? What are you doing?".

787
01:10:32,561 --> 01:10:36,356
"Do you want to meet me?
Whatever".

788
01:10:37,233 --> 01:10:39,234
"This Friday for dinner?"

789
01:10:40,110 --> 01:10:42,111
"Just to catch up".

790
01:10:46,700 --> 01:10:49,619
You really touch me whenever you feel like,
don't you?

791
01:10:50,162 --> 01:10:51,579
No, I don't.

792
01:10:52,957 --> 01:10:57,126
I touch you a fraction of how
often I'd like to.

793
01:10:58,754 --> 01:11:00,063
Why?

794
01:11:04,260 --> 01:11:05,969
Because I like you.

795
01:11:25,364 --> 01:11:26,990
I can't.

796
01:11:31,912 --> 01:11:35,915
I can't do anymore,
and look him in the eye.

797
01:11:48,721 --> 01:11:52,515
You just told me he's away with a woman
you got upset about.

798
01:11:57,104 --> 01:11:59,355
Michael isn't doing anything...

799
01:12:15,372 --> 01:12:17,957
I never told him about us.

800
01:12:19,168 --> 01:12:20,507
Even when -

801
01:12:21,347 --> 01:12:24,047
- I found the need to confess something.

802
01:12:24,214 --> 01:12:25,548
Which is when?

803
01:12:26,800 --> 01:12:29,010
When I'm drunk, or happy -

804
01:12:30,429 --> 01:12:32,847
- or after a fight, or in the middle of one -

805
01:12:32,973 --> 01:12:35,641
- when things slip out, this never does.

806
01:12:35,768 --> 01:12:38,019
Why?
Would he be angry?

807
01:12:40,981 --> 01:12:42,940
He'd have no right to be.

808
01:12:44,276 --> 01:12:45,818
I gave you up.

809
01:12:59,208 --> 01:13:00,875
So what's Helen like?

810
01:13:17,518 --> 01:13:19,394
We have another couple of hours -

811
01:13:20,354 --> 01:13:22,355
- I don't want to spend them talking
about Helen.

812
01:13:25,025 --> 01:13:26,484
Come...

813
01:13:29,772 --> 01:13:31,447
Jo...

814
01:13:35,035 --> 01:13:36,452
Come here...

815
01:16:26,290 --> 01:16:27,748
Jo...

816
01:16:33,130 --> 01:16:36,090
What time is it?
Six thirty.

817
01:17:03,619 --> 01:17:04,994
Laura...

818
01:17:05,162 --> 01:17:08,873
Michael, I don't need us to talk about it.

819
01:17:11,418 --> 01:17:13,669
Last night...
Michael, please.

820
01:17:14,838 --> 01:17:16,213
Just don't.

821
01:17:21,345 --> 01:17:23,387
I didn't think that would happen.

822
01:17:26,141 --> 01:17:27,933
Not even a second time?

823
01:18:39,726 --> 01:18:42,438
Well there's so much going on
right now, isn't it?

824
01:18:49,224 --> 01:18:52,184
What I wouldn't give to have tired
of you.

825
01:18:59,818 --> 01:19:02,912
Let me drop you off.
No, I'd rather walk.

826
01:19:03,021 --> 01:19:04,997
Are you sure?
Yes, it would be good for her.

827
01:19:04,998 --> 01:19:06,373
It would be good for me.

828
01:19:08,285 --> 01:19:11,746
Let's not do this in a big way, ok?
Please.

829
01:19:19,588 --> 01:19:21,005
See ya!

830
01:20:48,607 --> 01:20:50,400
<i>It's possible I overreacted.</i>

831
01:20:50,401 --> 01:20:51,794
<i>I know that. I know you.</i>

832
01:20:51,795 --> 01:20:53,181
<i>And I love you.
Jo.</i>

833
01:21:34,681 --> 01:21:36,432
Hey Andy, it's me.

834
01:21:38,435 --> 01:21:40,311
I need you to cover for me.

835
01:22:19,976 --> 01:22:21,727
Hey.
Hey.

836
01:22:21,853 --> 01:22:24,146
Are you ready?
Yeah. Where's Michael?

837
01:22:24,911 --> 01:22:26,411
He had to go back to New York.

838
01:22:27,617 --> 01:22:29,012
Is everything ok?

839
01:22:29,085 --> 01:22:31,670
Yeah, he left me a voicemail.

840
01:22:31,696 --> 01:22:33,822
I guess, Stuart needed him
to go back.

841
01:22:35,449 --> 01:22:36,825
Okay...

842
01:22:36,952 --> 01:22:38,452
I'll see you out front.

843
01:24:28,855 --> 01:24:30,164
Joey...

844
01:24:35,570 --> 01:24:37,196
What are you doing back?

845
01:24:38,323 --> 01:24:39,990
What's Lucy doing here?

846
01:24:40,950 --> 01:24:43,285
We got locked out of Andy's.

847
01:24:43,453 --> 01:24:45,913
Who?
Me and Lucy.

848
01:24:47,123 --> 01:24:48,457
When?

849
01:24:50,168 --> 01:24:55,089
Last night, when I went out to walk her.

850
01:24:55,673 --> 01:24:57,299
You've been crying, Jo?

851
01:24:58,384 --> 01:24:59,760
A bit.

852
01:25:02,597 --> 01:25:04,389
What are you doing back?

853
01:25:06,851 --> 01:25:08,560
We finished up early.

854
01:25:09,938 --> 01:25:12,272
Thought the presentation was today?

855
01:25:12,398 --> 01:25:15,317
No, we finished up early.

856
01:25:21,908 --> 01:25:23,742
I'm sorry about our fight.

857
01:25:26,996 --> 01:25:28,664
Yeah, so am I.

858
01:25:30,708 --> 01:25:33,836
Let's not talk about it, okay?

859
01:25:34,462 --> 01:25:39,675
Let's have a great lunch, let's walk.

860
01:25:40,468 --> 01:25:42,052
Let's make a day of it.

861
01:25:44,180 --> 01:25:45,514
Okay.

862
01:25:48,184 --> 01:25:49,560
Does she want to go out?

863
01:25:49,686 --> 01:25:51,478
Probably.

864
01:25:51,604 --> 01:25:54,731
I'll take her.
Come on.

865
01:26:05,660 --> 01:26:08,745
Are you okay?
Yeah.

866
01:26:21,134 --> 01:26:22,759
I love you.

867
01:26:52,000 --> 01:26:57,000
